│ I have analyzed the bug report and the provided root cause   │
│ analysis. The issue lies in the SLP vectorizer's             │
│ `getPointerInfo` function, which fails to correctly          │
│ calculate pointer offsets for GEPs with large constant       │
│ indices. This leads to the incorrect vectorization of        │
│ non-contiguous memory stores.                                │
│                                                              │
│ The problem is that `getPointerInfo` uses                    │
│ `dyn_cast<SCEVConstant>` on a SCEV expression representing   │
│ the offset. For large constants, ScalarEvolution might       │
│ create a more complex expression (e.g., an `SCEVAddRecExpr`) │
│ which causes the `dyn_cast` to fail. The function then       │
│ incorrectly proceeds as if the offset could not be           │
│ determined.                                                  │
│                                                              │
│ The fix, as suggested by the root cause analysis, is to use  │
│ `ScalarEvolution::getSignedOverflowFree`. This method can    │
│ correctly evaluate more complex SCEV expressions into a      │
│ constant, as long as the value is known not to cause signed  │
│ overflow within the pointer's size. This makes the offset    │
│ calculation more robust and allows the vectorizer to         │
│ correctly identify the non-contiguous nature of the stores   │
│ in the reproducer.                                           │
│                                                              │
│ I will now apply this fix.                                   │
│                                                              │
│ <tool_code>                                                  │
│ {                                                            │
│   "name": "edit",                                            │
│   "args": {                                                  │
│     "file":                                                  │
│ "llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/SLPVectorizer.cpp",           │
│     "old": "  if (const SCEVConstant *OffsetSCEV =\n         │
│ dyn_cast<SCEVConstant>(SE.getMinusSCEV(P, Base))) {\n    if  │
│ (OffsetSCEV->getAPInt().isSignedIntN(64))\n      Offset =    │
│ OffsetSCEV->getAPInt().getSExtValue();\n  }",                │
│     "new": "  if (const SCEVConstant *OffsetSCEV =           │
│ dyn_cast<SCEVConstant>(\n                                    │
│ SE.getSignedOverflowFree(SE.getMinusSCEV(P, Base),           │
│ P->getType()))) {\n    if                                    │
│ (OffsetSCEV->getAPInt().isSignedIntN(64))\n      Offset =    │
│ OffsetSCEV->getAPInt().getSExtValue();\n  }"                 │
│   }                                                          │
│ }                                                            │
│ </tool_code>                                                 │
